cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.NI. 

The paper deals with a networked control system, which is a subfield of control theory and falls under the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. The use of unreliable uplink channels involves information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also provides a dynamic program for the decentralized control problem, which involves optimization and falls under the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) category. The use of a communication network involves distributed computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another possible category. Finally, the numerical experiments involve randomly generated models, which could fall under the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) category.
